29// TODO(?): Move these to a common place (used in relayport too)
30const int RETRY_TIMEOUT = 50 * 1000; // 50 seconds
31
32// Stop logging errors in UDPPort::SendTo after we have logged
33// |kSendErrorLogLimit| messages. Start again after a successful send.
34const int kSendErrorLogLimit = 5;
35
36// Handles a binding request sent to the STUN server.
37class StunBindingRequest : public StunRequest {
38 public:
39 StunBindingRequest(UDPPort* port,
40 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
41 int64_t start_time)
42 : port_(port), server_addr_(addr), start_time_(start_time) {}
43
44 const rtc::SocketAddress& server_addr() const { return server_addr_; }
45
46 void Prepare(StunMessage* request) override {
47 request->SetType(STUN_BINDING_REQUEST);
48 }
49
50 void OnResponse(StunMessage* response) override {
51 const StunAddressAttribute* addr_attr =
52 response->GetAddress(STUN_ATTR_MAPPED_ADDRESS);
53 if (!addr_attr) {
54 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Binding response missing mapped address.";
55 } else if (addr_attr->family() != STUN_ADDRESS_IPV4 &&
56 addr_attr->family() != STUN_ADDRESS_IPV6) {
57 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Binding address has bad family";
58 } else {
59 rtc::SocketAddress addr(addr_attr->ipaddr(), addr_attr->port());
60 port_->OnStunBindingRequestSucceeded(this->Elapsed(), server_addr_, addr);
61 }
62
63 // The keep-alive requests will be stopped after its lifetime has passed.
64 if (WithinLifetime(rtc::TimeMillis())) {
65 port_->requests_.SendDelayed(
66 new StunBindingRequest(port_, server_addr_, start_time_),
67 port_->stun_keepalive_delay());
68 }
69 }
70
71 void OnErrorResponse(StunMessage* response) override {
72 const StunErrorCodeAttribute* attr = response->GetErrorCode();
73 if (!attr) {
74 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Missing binding response error code.";
75 } else {
76 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Binding error response:"
77 " class="
78 << attr->eclass() << " number=" << attr->number()
79 << " reason=" << attr->reason();
80 }
81
82 port_->OnStunBindingOrResolveRequestFailed(
83 server_addr_, attr ? attr->number() : STUN_ERROR_GLOBAL_FAILURE,
84 attr ? attr->reason()
85 : "STUN binding response with no error code attribute.");
86
87 int64_t now = rtc::TimeMillis();
88 if (WithinLifetime(now) &&
89 rtc::TimeDiff(now, start_time_) < RETRY_TIMEOUT) {
90 port_->requests_.SendDelayed(
91 new StunBindingRequest(port_, server_addr_, start_time_),
92 port_->stun_keepalive_delay());
93 }
94 }
95 void OnTimeout() override {
96 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Binding request timed out from "
97 << port_->GetLocalAddress().ToSensitiveString() << " ("
98 << port_->Network()->name() << ")";
99 port_->OnStunBindingOrResolveRequestFailed(
100 server_addr_, SERVER_NOT_REACHABLE_ERROR,
101 "STUN allocate request timed out.");
102 }
103
104 private:
105 // Returns true if |now| is within the lifetime of the request (a negative
106 // lifetime means infinite).
107 bool WithinLifetime(int64_t now) const {
108 int lifetime = port_->stun_keepalive_lifetime();
109 return lifetime < 0 || rtc::TimeDiff(now, start_time_) <= lifetime;
110 }
111
112 UDPPort* port_;
113 const rtc::SocketAddress server_addr_;
114
115 int64_t start_time_;
116};

118UDPPort::AddressResolver::AddressResolver(rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory)
119 : socket_factory_(factory) {}
120
121UDPPort::AddressResolver::~AddressResolver() {
122 for (ResolverMap::iterator it = resolvers_.begin(); it != resolvers_.end();
123 ++it) {
124 // TODO(guoweis): Change to asynchronous DNS resolution to prevent the hang
125 // when passing true to the Destroy() which is a safer way to avoid the code
126 // unloaded before the thread exits. Please see webrtc bug 5139.
127 it->second->Destroy(false);
128 }
129}
130
131void UDPPort::AddressResolver::Resolve(const rtc::SocketAddress& address) {
132 if (resolvers_.find(address) != resolvers_.end())
133 return;
134
135 rtc::AsyncResolverInterface* resolver =
136 socket_factory_->CreateAsyncResolver();
137 resolvers_.insert(std::pair<rtc::SocketAddress, rtc::AsyncResolverInterface*>(
138 address, resolver));
139
140 resolver->SignalDone.connect(this,
141 &UDPPort::AddressResolver::OnResolveResult);
142
143 resolver->Start(address);
144}
145
146bool UDPPort::AddressResolver::GetResolvedAddress(
147 const rtc::SocketAddress& input,
148 int family,
149 rtc::SocketAddress* output) const {
150 ResolverMap::const_iterator it = resolvers_.find(input);
151 if (it == resolvers_.end())
152 return false;
153
154 return it->second->GetResolvedAddress(family, output);
155}
156
157void UDPPort::AddressResolver::OnResolveResult(
158 rtc::AsyncResolverInterface* resolver) {
159 for (ResolverMap::iterator it = resolvers_.begin(); it != resolvers_.end();
160 ++it) {
161 if (it->second == resolver) {
162 SignalDone(it->first, resolver->GetError());
163 return;
164 }
165 }
166}

168UDPPort::UDPPort(rtc::Thread* thread,
169 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory,
170 rtc::Network* network,
171 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
172 const std::string& username,
173 const std::string& password,
174 const std::string& origin,
175 bool emit_local_for_anyaddress)
176 : Port(thread, LOCAL_PORT_TYPE, factory, network, username, password),
177 requests_(thread),
178 socket_(socket),
179 error_(0),
180 ready_(false),
181 stun_keepalive_delay_(STUN_KEEPALIVE_INTERVAL),
182 dscp_(rtc::DSCP_NO_CHANGE),
183 emit_local_for_anyaddress_(emit_local_for_anyaddress) {
184 requests_.set_origin(origin);
185}

190 uint16_t min_port,
191 uint16_t max_port,
192 const std::string& username,

200 min_port,

202 username,
203 password),
204 requests_(thread),
205 socket_(nullptr),
206 error_(0),

209 dscp_(rtc::DSCP_NO_CHANGE),
210 emit_local_for_anyaddress_(emit_local_for_anyaddress) {
211 requests_.set_origin(origin);
212}

214bool UDPPort::Init() {
215 stun_keepalive_lifetime_ = GetStunKeepaliveLifetime();
216 if (!SharedSocket()) {
217 RTC_DCHECK(socket_ == nullptr);
218 socket_ = socket_factory()->CreateUdpSocket(
219 rtc::SocketAddress(Network()->GetBestIP(), 0), min_port(), max_port());
220 if (!socket_) {
221 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString() << ": UDP socket creation failed";
222 return false;
223 }
224 socket_->SignalReadPacket.connect(this, &UDPPort::OnReadPacket);
225 }
226 socket_->SignalSentPacket.connect(this, &UDPPort::OnSentPacket);
227 socket_->SignalReadyToSend.connect(this, &UDPPort::OnReadyToSend);
228 socket_->SignalAddressReady.connect(this, &UDPPort::OnLocalAddressReady);
229 requests_.SignalSendPacket.connect(this, &UDPPort::OnSendPacket);
230 return true;
231}
232
233UDPPort::~UDPPort() {
234 if (!SharedSocket())
235 delete socket_;
236}
237
238void UDPPort::PrepareAddress() {
239 RTC_DCHECK(requests_.empty());
240 if (socket_->GetState() == rtc::AsyncPacketSocket::STATE_BOUND) {
241 OnLocalAddressReady(socket_, socket_->GetLocalAddress());
242 }
243}
244
245void UDPPort::MaybePrepareStunCandidate() {
246 // Sending binding request to the STUN server if address is available to
247 // prepare STUN candidate.
248 if (!server_addresses_.empty()) {
249 SendStunBindingRequests();
250 } else {
251 // Port is done allocating candidates.
252 MaybeSetPortCompleteOrError();
253 }
254}
255
256Connection* UDPPort::CreateConnection(const Candidate& address,
257 CandidateOrigin origin) {
258 if (!SupportsProtocol(address.protocol())) {
259 return nullptr;
260 }
261
262 if (!IsCompatibleAddress(address.address())) {
263 return nullptr;
264 }
265
266 // In addition to DCHECK-ing the non-emptiness of local candidates, we also
267 // skip this Port with null if there are latent bugs to violate it; otherwise
268 // it would lead to a crash when accessing the local candidate of the
269 // connection that would be created below.
270 if (Candidates().empty()) {
271 RTC_NOTREACHED();
272 return nullptr;
273 }
274 // When the socket is shared, the srflx candidate is gathered by the UDPPort.
275 // The assumption here is that
276 // 1) if the IP concealment with mDNS is not enabled, the gathering of the
277 // host candidate of this port (which is synchronous),
278 // 2) or otherwise if enabled, the start of name registration of the host
279 // candidate (as the start of asynchronous gathering)
280 // is always before the gathering of a srflx candidate (and any prflx
281 // candidate).
282 //
283 // See also the definition of MdnsNameRegistrationStatus::kNotStarted in
284 // port.h.
285 RTC_DCHECK(!SharedSocket() || Candidates()[0].type() == LOCAL_PORT_TYPE ||
286 mdns_name_registration_status() !=
287 MdnsNameRegistrationStatus::kNotStarted);
288
289 Connection* conn = new ProxyConnection(this, 0, address);
290 AddOrReplaceConnection(conn);
291 return conn;
292}
293
294int UDPPort::SendTo(const void* data,
295 size_t size,
296 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
297 const rtc::PacketOptions& options,
298 bool payload) {
299 rtc::PacketOptions modified_options(options);
300 CopyPortInformationToPacketInfo(&modified_options.info_signaled_after_sent);
301 int sent = socket_->SendTo(data, size, addr, modified_options);
302 if (sent < 0) {
303 error_ = socket_->GetError();
304 // Rate limiting added for crbug.com/856088.
305 // TODO(webrtc:9622): Use general rate limiting mechanism once it exists.
306 if (send_error_count_ < kSendErrorLogLimit) {
307 ++send_error_count_;
308 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": UDP send of " << size
309 << " bytes to host " << addr.ToSensitiveString() << " ("
310 << addr.ToResolvedSensitiveString()
311 << ") failed with error " << error_;
312 }
313 } else {
314 send_error_count_ = 0;
315 }
316 return sent;
317}

370void UDPPort::OnLocalAddressReady(rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
371 const rtc::SocketAddress& address) {
372 // When adapter enumeration is disabled and binding to the any address, the
373 // default local address will be issued as a candidate instead if
374 // |emit_local_for_anyaddress| is true. This is to allow connectivity for
375 // applications which absolutely requires a HOST candidate.
376 rtc::SocketAddress addr = address;
377
378 // If MaybeSetDefaultLocalAddress fails, we keep the "any" IP so that at
379 // least the port is listening.
380 MaybeSetDefaultLocalAddress(&addr);
381
382 AddAddress(addr, addr, rtc::SocketAddress(), UDP_PROTOCOL_NAME, "", "",
383 LOCAL_PORT_TYPE, ICE_TYPE_PREFERENCE_HOST, 0, "", false);
384 MaybePrepareStunCandidate();
385}
386
387void UDPPort::PostAddAddress(bool is_final) {
388 MaybeSetPortCompleteOrError();
389}
390
391void UDPPort::OnReadPacket(rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
392 const char* data,
393 size_t size,
394 const rtc::SocketAddress& remote_addr,
395 const int64_t& packet_time_us) {
396 RTC_DCHECK(socket == socket_);
397 RTC_DCHECK(!remote_addr.IsUnresolvedIP());
398
399 // Look for a response from the STUN server.
400 // Even if the response doesn't match one of our outstanding requests, we
401 // will eat it because it might be a response to a retransmitted packet, and
402 // we already cleared the request when we got the first response.
403 if (server_addresses_.find(remote_addr) != server_addresses_.end()) {
404 requests_.CheckResponse(data, size);
405 return;
406 }
407
408 if (Connection* conn = GetConnection(remote_addr)) {
409 conn->OnReadPacket(data, size, packet_time_us);
410 } else {
411 Port::OnReadPacket(data, size, remote_addr, PROTO_UDP);
412 }
413}

423
424void UDPPort::SendStunBindingRequests() {
425 // We will keep pinging the stun server to make sure our NAT pin-hole stays
426 // open until the deadline (specified in SendStunBindingRequest).
427 RTC_DCHECK(requests_.empty());
428
429 for (ServerAddresses::const_iterator it = server_addresses_.begin();
430 it != server_addresses_.end(); ++it) {
431 SendStunBindingRequest(*it);
432 }
433}
434
435void UDPPort::ResolveStunAddress(const rtc::SocketAddress& stun_addr) {
436 if (!resolver_) {
437 resolver_.reset(new AddressResolver(socket_factory()));
438 resolver_->SignalDone.connect(this, &UDPPort::OnResolveResult);
439 }
440
441 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Starting STUN host lookup for "
442 << stun_addr.ToSensitiveString();
443 resolver_->Resolve(stun_addr);
444}
445
446void UDPPort::OnResolveResult(const rtc::SocketAddress& input, int error) {
447 RTC_DCHECK(resolver_.get() != nullptr);
448
449 rtc::SocketAddress resolved;
450 if (error != 0 || !resolver_->GetResolvedAddress(
451 input, Network()->GetBestIP().family(), &resolved)) {
452 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString()
453 << ": StunPort: stun host lookup received error "
454 << error;
455 OnStunBindingOrResolveRequestFailed(input, SERVER_NOT_REACHABLE_ERROR,
456 "STUN host lookup received error.");
457 return;
458 }
459
460 server_addresses_.erase(input);
461
462 if (server_addresses_.find(resolved) == server_addresses_.end()) {
463 server_addresses_.insert(resolved);
464 SendStunBindingRequest(resolved);
465 }
466}
467
468void UDPPort::SendStunBindingRequest(const rtc::SocketAddress& stun_addr) {
469 if (stun_addr.IsUnresolvedIP()) {
470 ResolveStunAddress(stun_addr);
471
472 } else if (socket_->GetState() == rtc::AsyncPacketSocket::STATE_BOUND) {
473 // Check if |server_addr_| is compatible with the port's ip.
474 if (IsCompatibleAddress(stun_addr)) {
475 requests_.Send(
476 new StunBindingRequest(this, stun_addr, rtc::TimeMillis()));
477 } else {
478 // Since we can't send stun messages to the server, we should mark this
479 // port ready.
480 const char* reason = "STUN server address is incompatible.";
481 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << reason;
482 OnStunBindingOrResolveRequestFailed(stun_addr, SERVER_NOT_REACHABLE_ERROR,
483 reason);
484 }
485 }
486}
487
488bool UDPPort::MaybeSetDefaultLocalAddress(rtc::SocketAddress* addr) const {
489 if (!addr->IsAnyIP() || !emit_local_for_anyaddress_ ||
490 !Network()->default_local_address_provider()) {
491 return true;
492 }
493 rtc::IPAddress default_address;
494 bool result =
495 Network()->default_local_address_provider()->GetDefaultLocalAddress(
496 addr->family(), &default_address);
497 if (!result || default_address.IsNil()) {
498 return false;
499 }
500
501 addr->SetIP(default_address);
502 return true;
503}
504
505void UDPPort::OnStunBindingRequestSucceeded(
506 int rtt_ms,
507 const rtc::SocketAddress& stun_server_addr,
508 const rtc::SocketAddress& stun_reflected_addr) {
509 RTC_DCHECK(stats_.stun_binding_responses_received <
510 stats_.stun_binding_requests_sent);
511 stats_.stun_binding_responses_received++;
512 stats_.stun_binding_rtt_ms_total += rtt_ms;
513 stats_.stun_binding_rtt_ms_squared_total += rtt_ms * rtt_ms;
514 if (bind_request_succeeded_servers_.find(stun_server_addr) !=
515 bind_request_succeeded_servers_.end()) {
516 return;
517 }
518 bind_request_succeeded_servers_.insert(stun_server_addr);
519 // If socket is shared and |stun_reflected_addr| is equal to local socket
520 // address, or if the same address has been added by another STUN server,
521 // then discarding the stun address.
522 // For STUN, related address is the local socket address.
523 if ((!SharedSocket() || stun_reflected_addr != socket_->GetLocalAddress()) &&
524 !HasCandidateWithAddress(stun_reflected_addr)) {
525 rtc::SocketAddress related_address = socket_->GetLocalAddress();
526 // If we can't stamp the related address correctly, empty it to avoid leak.
527 if (!MaybeSetDefaultLocalAddress(&related_address)) {
528 related_address =
529 rtc::EmptySocketAddressWithFamily(related_address.family());
530 }
531
532 rtc::StringBuilder url;
533 url << "stun:" << stun_server_addr.ipaddr().ToString() << ":"
534 << stun_server_addr.port();
535 AddAddress(stun_reflected_addr, socket_->GetLocalAddress(), related_address,
536 UDP_PROTOCOL_NAME, "", "", STUN_PORT_TYPE,
537 ICE_TYPE_PREFERENCE_SRFLX, 0, url.str(), false);
538 }
539 MaybeSetPortCompleteOrError();
540}
541
542void UDPPort::OnStunBindingOrResolveRequestFailed(
543 const rtc::SocketAddress& stun_server_addr,
544 int error_code,
545 const std::string& reason) {
546 rtc::StringBuilder url;
547 url << "stun:" << stun_server_addr.ToString();
548 SignalCandidateError(
549 this, IceCandidateErrorEvent(GetLocalAddress().HostAsSensitiveURIString(),
550 GetLocalAddress().port(), url.str(),
551 error_code, reason));
552 if (bind_request_failed_servers_.find(stun_server_addr) !=
553 bind_request_failed_servers_.end()) {
554 return;
555 }
556 bind_request_failed_servers_.insert(stun_server_addr);
557 MaybeSetPortCompleteOrError();
558}
559
560void UDPPort::MaybeSetPortCompleteOrError() {
561 if (mdns_name_registration_status() ==
562 MdnsNameRegistrationStatus::kInProgress) {
563 return;
564 }
565
566 if (ready_) {
567 return;
568 }
569
570 // Do not set port ready if we are still waiting for bind responses.
571 const size_t servers_done_bind_request =
572 bind_request_failed_servers_.size() +
573 bind_request_succeeded_servers_.size();
574 if (server_addresses_.size() != servers_done_bind_request) {
575 return;
576 }
577
578 // Setting ready status.
579 ready_ = true;
580
581 // The port is "completed" if there is no stun server provided, or the bind
582 // request succeeded for any stun server, or the socket is shared.
583 if (server_addresses_.empty() || bind_request_succeeded_servers_.size() > 0 ||
584 SharedSocket()) {
585 SignalPortComplete(this);
586 } else {
587 SignalPortError(this);
588 }
589}
590
591// TODO(?): merge this with SendTo above.
592void UDPPort::OnSendPacket(const void* data, size_t size, StunRequest* req) {
593 StunBindingRequest* sreq = static_cast<StunBindingRequest*>(req);
594 rtc::PacketOptions options(StunDscpValue());
595 options.info_signaled_after_sent.packet_type = rtc::PacketType::kStunMessage;
596 CopyPortInformationToPacketInfo(&options.info_signaled_after_sent);
597 if (socket_->SendTo(data, size, sreq->server_addr(), options) < 0) {
598 RTC_LOG_ERR_EX(LERROR, socket_->GetError())
599 << "UDP send of " << size << " bytes to host "
600 << sreq->server_addr().ToSensitiveString() << " ("
601 << sreq->server_addr().ToResolvedSensitiveString()
602 << ") failed with error " << error_;
603 }
604 stats_.stun_binding_requests_sent++;
605}
606
607bool UDPPort::HasCandidateWithAddress(const rtc::SocketAddress& addr) const {
608 const std::vector<Candidate>& existing_candidates = Candidates();
609 std::vector<Candidate>::const_iterator it = existing_candidates.begin();
610 for (; it != existing_candidates.end(); ++it) {
611 if (it->address() == addr)
612 return true;
613 }
614 return false;
615}

617std::unique_ptr<StunPort> StunPort::Create(
618 rtc::Thread* thread,
619 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory,
620 rtc::Network* network,
621 uint16_t min_port,
622 uint16_t max_port,
623 const std::string& username,
624 const std::string& password,
625 const ServerAddresses& servers,
626 const std::string& origin,
627 absl::optional<int> stun_keepalive_interval) {
628 // Using `new` to access a non-public constructor.
629 auto port = absl::WrapUnique(new StunPort(thread, factory, network, min_port,
630 max_port, username, password,
631 servers, origin));
632 port->set_stun_keepalive_delay(stun_keepalive_interval);
633 if (!port->Init()) {
634 return nullptr;
635 }
636 return port;
637}

639StunPort::StunPort(rtc::Thread* thread,
640 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory,
641 rtc::Network* network,
642 uint16_t min_port,
643 uint16_t max_port,
644 const std::string& username,
645 const std::string& password,
646 const ServerAddresses& servers,
647 const std::string& origin)
648 : UDPPort(thread,
649 factory,
650 network,
651 min_port,
652 max_port,
653 username,
654 password,
655 origin,
656 false) {
657 // UDPPort will set these to local udp, updating these to STUN.
658 set_type(STUN_PORT_TYPE);
659 set_server_addresses(servers);
660}
